					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">zeroone wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What's the concept behind the hack?</div><br />Micro Machines reads $2004 around dot 320.  If the read occurs before dot 320, it needs to see a value with the high bit set (implemented properly, the read would return $FF because it would take place while the PPU is fetching from an empty sprite slot).  If the read occurs &gt;= dot 320, it needs to see a value without the high bit set (which it does, because the first byte in secondary OAM is &lt; 0x80).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Is there an accurate way to do this?</div><br />Yep.  Implement it as described on the wiki.</div>

					
