				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><ul><li>If rendering is disabled, and the current VRAM address is $0000-$3EFF, the PPU will output the color at $3F00. </li><li>If rendering is disabled, and the current VRAM address is $3F00, the PPU will output the color at $3F00. </li><li>If rendering is disabled, and the current VRAM address is $3F01, the PPU will output the color at $3F01. </li><li>If rendering is disabled, and the current VRAM address is $3F02, the PPU will output the color at $3F02. </li><li>If rendering is disabled, and the current VRAM address is $3F03, the PPU will output the color at $3F03. </li></ul><br />It stores a table of colors at $3F00-$3F1F and expects to be able to switch to the next color by reading one byte from or writing one byte to the VRAM data port, which advances the VRAM address by 1.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
